CONSTRAINTS : are rules appiled to column in database
Types :


(1) UNIQUE - Ensure all values in column are different
(2) NOT NULL -  Ensure a column cannot have null values
(3) PRIMARY KEY - Uniquely identifies each row in table, combines NOT NULL and UNIQUE
(4) FOREIGN KEY - Maintains referential integrity between tables
(5) CHECK - Restrict values with a specific condition
(6) DEFAULT - sets a default value for a column 